"Checks if the '**lhs**' is **greater than** the '**rhs**'. The value of "
"the '**comparisonType**' field is **\"greater_than\"**."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:183
msgid "Greater Than or Equal (>=)"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:185
msgid ""
"Checks if the '**lhs**' is **greater than or equal to** the '**rhs**'. "
"The value of the '**comparisonType**' field is "
"**\"greater_equal_than\"**."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:204
msgid "Logical Operators"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:206
msgid ""
"These operators are used to combine or negate conditions. Each logical "
"operator involves a list of operands, with each operand defining another "
"operator."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:209
msgid ""
"The type of the logical operator is defined through the field "
"'**logicalType**', the content of which is a string. The logical types "
"are defined below:"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:214
msgid "Negation (not)"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:218
msgid "Negation needs only one operand."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:220
msgid ""
"Negates a operand. The value of the '**logicalType**' field is "
"**\"negation\"**."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:238
msgid "Conjunction (and)"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:240
msgid ""
"Checks if all operands are true. The value of the '**logicalType**' field"
" is **\"conjunction\"**."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:264
msgid "Disjunction (or)"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:266
msgid ""
"Checks if at least one operand is true. The value of the "
"'**logicalType**' field is **\"disjunction\"**."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:290
msgid "Property Operators"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:292
msgid ""
"These operators are used to extract the characteristics of schema "
"properties; such as the value associated with the property in the "
"configuration and checking for the possibility that the property is null,"
" or in the case of an array property, the size of the array or the value "
"of an array element."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:296
msgid ""
"All property operators have a field called '**relativePath**', where the "
"path to the desired property is defined by a list of strings."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:299
msgid ""
"The property element to be extracted is defined through the field "
"'**propertyElement**', whose content is a string. The property elements "
"are defined below:"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:304
msgid "Value of the Property"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:306
msgid ""
"Extracts the value associated with the property in the configuration. The"
" value of the '**propertyElement**' field is **\"value\"**."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:324
msgid "Item of the Property"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:326
msgid ""
"Extracts the value of the desired item of the property in the "
"configuration. The value of the '**propertyElement**' field is "
"**\"item\"**."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:328
msgid ""
"The selection of the item is defined through the '**selectedItem**' "
"field, which can be defined as a positive integer or as an operator."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:362
msgid "Size of the Property"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:364
msgid ""
"Extracts the size of the property defined in the configuration. The value"
" of the '**propertyElement**' field is **\"size\"**."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:382
msgid "Null Status of the Property"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:386
msgid "Always returns a boolean value"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:388
msgid ""
"Extracts the possibility of being or not being null of the property. The "
"value of the '**propertyElement**' field is **\"nullProperty\"**."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:406
msgid "Constant Operators"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:408
msgid ""
"These operators are used to return constant values independent of the "
"configuration used. The constant value is defined through the '**value**'"
" field, which takes values of a basic type such as an integer, a string, "
"a boolean or a floating point number."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:443
msgid "Arithmetical Operators"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:445
msgid ""
"In JSON Schema, arithmetical operators are used to perform basic "
"arithmetic operations and define numeric constraints. Each arithmetic "
"operation consists of two parts: the left-hand side (`lhs`) and the "
"right-hand side (`rhs`). On both sides another operator must be defined."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:449
msgid ""
"The type of the arithmetic operator is defined by the field "
"'**arithmeticalType**', whose content is a string. The arithmetic "
"operator types are defined below:"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:454
msgid "Subtract (-)"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:456
msgid ""
"The subtract operator is used to subtract one number from another. The "
"value of the '**arithmeticalType**' field is **\"subtract\"**."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:475
msgid "Addition (+)"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:477
msgid ""
"The addition operator is used to sum two numbers. The value of the "
"'**arithmeticalType**' field is **\"addition\"**."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:496
msgid "Multiply (*)"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:498
msgid ""
"The multiply operator is used to multiply two numbers. The value of the "
"'**arithmeticalType**' field is **\"multiply\"**."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:517
msgid "Division (/)"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:519
msgid ""
"The division operator is used to divide one number by another. The value "
"of the '**arithmeticalType**' field is **\"division\"**."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:538
msgid "Module (%)"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:540
msgid ""
"The module operator is used to find the remainder of the division of one "
"number by another. The value of the '**arithmeticalType**' field is "
"**\"module\"**."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:559
msgid "Conditionals of JSON Schema"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:561
msgid ""
"Conditionals in JSON schemas function as schema modifiers based on the "
"values of the configuration used in the validation. Each conditional is "
"defined by a dictionary (or object). These conditionals, like a "
"conditional in programming, have three distinct parts, which are defined "
"in three fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:566
msgid "Condition"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:568
msgid ""
"The '**condition**' field is in charge of deciding which block of the "
"conditional will modify the schema, the "
":ref:`json_validator/advanced_features:then block` or the "
":ref:`json_validator/advanced_features:else block`."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:571
msgid ""
"This field is defined by the use of operators. The result of the operator"
" resolution shall be evaluated as a condition. For more information on "
"operators, see the :ref:`json_validator/advanced_features:operators of "
"json schema` section."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:575
msgid "Then Block"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:577
msgid ""
"The block defined in the '**then**' field shall be applied in case the "
"conditional condition is true."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:579
msgid ""
"This block is defined by a dictionary (or object), which has three fields"
" to be defined, as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:581
msgid "**workingPath**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:585
msgid ""
"The '**workingPath**' field is optional. Its default value is the height "
"within the scheme in which the conditional is defined."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:587
msgid ""
"It is defined as a list of strings, which indicates the relative path to "
"the current position within the schema where the modification is to be "
"applied."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:589
msgid ""
"This field is necessary because it may be the case that the zone where "
"the modification is to be applied is at a different height from the zone "
"where the values for the resolution of the condition are obtained."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:591
msgid "**add**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:593
msgid ""
"The '**add**' field is defined as a dictionary (or object), in which "
"different fields are defined depending on the additions to be made to the"
" schema. The available modification fields are the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:595
#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:603
msgid "**nullProperty**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:597
msgid ""
"The purpose of this field is to activate the possibility of a schema "
"element to have a null value in the configuration. The way to define this"
" field is through a list of strings indicating the names of the affected "
"properties."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:599
msgid "**remove**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:601
msgid ""
"The '**remove**' field is defined as a dictionary (or object), in which "
"different fields are defined depending on the deletions to be made in the"
" schema. The following modification fields are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:605
msgid ""
"The purpose of this field is to disable the possibility that a schema "
"element can take a null value in the configuration. The way to define "
"this field is through a list of strings indicating the names of the "
"affected properties."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:609
msgid "Else Block"
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:611
msgid ""
"The block defined in the \"**else**\" field shall be applied in case the "
"conditional condition is false."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:613
msgid ""
"The structure of this block is exactly the same as in the "
":ref:`json_validator/advanced_features:then block` section."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:616
msgid ""
"In the case of having defined a pattern-based conditional, the above "
"structure is maintained in its entirety except for a single addition, the"
" possibility of using the value that matches the pattern."
msgstr ""

#: ../json_validator/advanced_features.rst:619
msgid ""
"This value can be used within the path defined by the '**workingPath**' "
"field as well as in the schema modification fields, such as "
"'**nullProperty**'. To use this value, the string **\"<pattern>\"** must "
"be placed, which will be replaced by the value matching the pattern "
"automatically within the validator."
msgstr ""

